1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,800
Most AI agent workflows

2
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,700
trust what a model says it is.

3
00:00:03,700 --> 00:00:05,240
Sol Ultra Gearbox

4
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:07,100
verifies what actually ran.

5
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:08,780
It routes Codex work to

6
00:00:08,780 --> 00:00:10,900
typed Sol, Terra, and Luna roles.

7
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:12,700
Then it checks the real model,

8
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:14,460
reasoning effort, sandbox,

9
00:00:14,460 --> 00:00:16,180
lineage, token usage,

10
00:00:16,180 --> 00:00:17,560
and filesystem scope from

11
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,233
persisted runtime metadata.

12
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,560
If anything is missing or

13
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:22,433
mismatched, it fails closed.

14
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:24,080
The built-in doctor validates

15
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:25,540
six role profiles.

16
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:27,280
Dry-run previews global changes,

17
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:29,167
while managed apply includes rollback.

18
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:31,220
This release passed twenty-three tests

19
00:00:31,220 --> 00:00:33,320
and a six-role runtime smoke test.

20
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:35,500
If your team needs multi-agent workflows

21
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,340
you can audit, reproduce, and reverse,

22
00:00:37,340 --> 00:00:38,900
try Sol Ultra Gearbox on GitHub.
